# HOF Chatwoot — Cursor AI Rules
# Chatwoot open-source fork customized for HOF Immigration internal use
# MIT License — internal use only, not for resale

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
This is a fork of Chatwoot (https://github.com/chatwoot/chatwoot) — an open-source
omnichannel customer support platform. HOF Immigration is customizing it for internal
WhatsApp-based case management and compliance tracking.

**Key context:**
- Original repo: https://github.com/chatwoot/chatwoot
- Our use case: Case managers chatting with immigration clients over WhatsApp
- Primary concern: Compliance visibility — admins must see all conversations
- Stack: Ruby on Rails (backend) + Vue.js (frontend) + PostgreSQL + Redis (Valkey)
- Deployment: Railway.app with custom domain inbox.hofmigration.com

---

## TECH STACK — UNDERSTAND BEFORE TOUCHING ANYTHING

### Backend
- Ruby on Rails 7.x (API + server-side rendering)
- Sidekiq (background jobs via Redis)
- PostgreSQL (primary database)
- Redis/Valkey (queues, caching, ActionCable)
- Action Cable (WebSockets for real-time)

### Frontend
- Vue.js 3 (component framework)
- Vite (build tool)
- Pinia (state management)
- Tailwind CSS + custom design tokens

### Key directories to understand first:
```
app/
  controllers/    → Rails API controllers
  models/         → ActiveRecord models
  jobs/           → Sidekiq background jobs
  views/          → Mailer templates (email)
  javascript/     → Vue.js frontend
    components/   → Reusable Vue components
    views/        → Page-level Vue components
    store/        → Pinia state stores
config/
  routes.rb       → All API and web routes
  database.yml    → DB configuration
db/
  schema.rb       → Current DB schema (source of truth)
  migrate/        → All migrations
enterprise/       → ENTERPRISE LICENSE — READ RULES BELOW
spec/             → RSpec tests
```


## STRICT RULES — READ BEFORE ANY CHANGE

### ❌ NEVER TOUCH — ASK USER FIRST:
```
enterprise/                   → Separate license, do not touch
db/schema.rb                  → Never edit directly, only via migrations
config/credentials.yml.enc    → Encrypted secrets
Gemfile.lock                  → Only changes via bundle install
yarn.lock                     → Only changes via yarn install
.github/                      → CI/CD workflows
spec/                         → Do not break existing tests
```

### ⚠️ TOUCH WITH EXTREME CAUTION — ALWAYS ASK USER:
```
config/routes.rb              → Adding routes = ok, removing = ask
app/models/user.rb            → Core auth model — very sensitive
app/models/account.rb         → Multi-tenancy core
app/models/conversation.rb    → Core messaging model
app/models/message.rb         → Core message model
app/controllers/api/          → Existing API endpoints — don't break
db/migrate/                   → Never edit existing migrations, only add new ones
```

### ✅ SAFE TO ADD/MODIFY FREELY:
```
app/controllers/api/v2/       → New API endpoints (use v2 namespace)
app/jobs/                     → New background jobs
app/mailers/                  → New email templates
app/views/mailers/            → Email HTML templates
app/javascript/views/         → New pages/views
app/javascript/components/    → New UI components
config/locales/               → Translation strings
lib/tasks/                    → Custom rake tasks
db/migrate/ (NEW files only)  → New migrations
```

---

## HOF-SPECIFIC CUSTOMIZATIONS — CONTEXT FOR AI

We are building these features ON TOP of Chatwoot:

### 1. SLA / Response Time Alerts (PRIORITY)
- If an agent has not replied to a conversation in X hours → send email to admin
- Location to build: `app/jobs/hof_sla_check_job.rb` (new file)
- Trigger: Sidekiq scheduled job every 30 minutes
- Do NOT modify existing notification system — add alongside it

### 2. HubSpot Sync (PLANNED)
- When conversation is resolved → update HubSpot deal stage
- New webhook handler: `app/controllers/api/v2/hof/hubspot_controller.rb`
- Reference: HOF uses HubSpot Sales Pro

### 3. Immigration Case Timeline (PLANNED)
- Custom attributes on conversations: visa_type, case_stage, assigned_date
- Use Chatwoot's existing custom_attributes system — do not create new tables

### 4. Compliance Reports (PLANNED)
- Admin-only dashboard showing agent response metrics
- Use existing Chatwoot reports infrastructure

